What is java?
java was developed by James Gosling at sun Microsystems in 1995 and later acquired by oracle
Java is a class based object oriented programming language
compliled java code can run on all platforms that supports java without the need for recompilation (Write Once Run Anywhere)
Widely used for developing applications for desktop , web and mobile devices

What is java used for?

Mobile App Development
Desktop GUI Applications
Web-based Applications
Gaming Applications
Big Data Technologies
Distributed Applications
Cloud-based Applications
IoT Applications

